@startuml Captraex_Website_TrustBoundaries
title Captraex Website - Trust Boundaries and Deployment Controls
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam wrapWidth 180

legend top right
  **Lane Semantics**
  |<#FFCCCC> Light Red | Untrusted user-controlled zone |
  |<#FFE6CC> Light Orange | Third-party / internet transit |
  |<#E6F2FF> Light Blue | Captraex trusted infrastructure |
endlegend

|#FFCCCC|Visitor + Browser Runtime|
start
:Load captraex.com pages;
:Execute static JS bundle in browser;
if (Preview mode enabled?) then (yes)
  :Evaluate site-auth cookie and\nclient-side password logic;
endif
:Click Sign in / Start trial CTA;

|#E6F2FF|Azure Static Web Apps (Website)|
:Serve immutable static export;
:Apply HSTS, CSP, anti-framing headers;
:Expose pricing and CTA pages;

|#FFE6CC|External Service Hand-offs|
:Redirect users to app.captraex.com;
:POST checkout request to api.captraex.com;
:Redirect to checkout.stripe.com;

|#E6F2FF|GitHub Actions CI/CD|
:Checkout repository source;
:Install dependencies (npm ci);
:Build static site artifact;
:Deploy using Azure Static Web Apps API token;

if (CI token/workflow compromised?) then (yes)
  |#FFCCCC|Threat Outcome|
  :Publish malicious site build;
  :Inject phishing redirect or hostile script;
  :Serve tampered content from trusted domain;
endif

|#E6F2FF|Security Operations|
:Monitor security headers in production;
:Rotate deploy token and review workflow access;
:Validate redirect host allowlists;
stop
@enduml
